1
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:04,920
Bhrugen: We have seen ViewBag in the last video.

2
00:00:04,920 --> 00:00:08,730
Next, we want to see how we can accomplish the same things

3
00:00:08,730 --> 00:00:10,830
with ViewData.

4
00:00:10,830 --> 00:00:13,110
ViewData also transfers the data

5
00:00:13,110 --> 00:00:16,680
from Controller to View, and not vice-versa.

6
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:19,710
And again, it is ideal for the situation

7
00:00:19,710 --> 00:00:23,790
where the temporary data is not in a model.

8
00:00:23,790 --> 00:00:27,480
ViewData is derived from ViewDataDictionary,

9
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,910
which is a dictionary type.

10
00:00:29,910 --> 00:00:34,050
ViewData value must be type casted before use.

11
00:00:34,050 --> 00:00:38,070
Like, if we go back, when we were using ViewBag right here,

12
00:00:38,070 --> 00:00:40,740
we did not have to cast that data.

13
00:00:40,740 --> 00:00:42,720
It was all dynamic.

14
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:44,790
But when we use ViewData,

15
00:00:44,790 --> 00:00:48,483
we will have to cast that before we use the value.

16
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:52,560
And lastly, the ViewBags life only lasts

17
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:55,230
during the current http request,

18
00:00:55,230 --> 00:00:59,430
and ViewData values will be null if redirection occurs,

19
00:00:59,430 --> 00:01:01,500
similar to ViewBag.

20
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:04,560
So there are quite a few things that are similar here

21
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:07,560
but let us see that with an example.

22
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:10,320
First, we have to go back to the Controller.

23
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,390
Let me comment this out.

24
00:01:12,390 --> 00:01:14,670
Copy that and paste it here.

25
00:01:14,670 --> 00:01:18,990
Rather than ViewBag, we want to use ViewData.

26
00:01:18,990 --> 00:01:21,930
If you use dot there, it will not work.

27
00:01:21,930 --> 00:01:24,930
You have to define that in a square bracket.

28
00:01:24,930 --> 00:01:28,353
And what is the key value? Like in a dictionary.

29
00:01:29,460 --> 00:01:32,733
That is how you assign a value to ViewData.

30
00:01:33,810 --> 00:01:38,010
Now the question is how do you access that inside view?

31
00:01:38,010 --> 00:01:39,630
When we were using ViewBag,

32
00:01:39,630 --> 00:01:41,940
we did not have to do conversion,

33
00:01:41,940 --> 00:01:46,260
but with ViewData we will have to do some conversion here.

34
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:51,260
So we will use the @ sign and we will save ViewData here.

35
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:54,990
Write the key name, let me go back and copy that

36
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:57,540
to avoid any spelling mistake.

37
00:01:57,540 --> 00:02:00,900
And then we have to explicitly convert that.

38
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:02,760
So we will say as,

39
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:07,203
and this will be an IEnumerable of SelectListItem.

40
00:02:09,180 --> 00:02:11,280
With that, the errors go away

41
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:15,810
and you can see how ViewData might be a little inconvenient

42
00:02:15,810 --> 00:02:18,033
as compared to ViewBag.

43
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:22,230
But with that, everything should work the same.

44
00:02:22,230 --> 00:02:26,223
Let me restart the application and see that in action.

45
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:31,680
We go to create new product, and perfect.

46
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,570
That is functional.

47
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:36,370
But there is one more thing that you should be aware of.

48
00:02:37,230 --> 00:02:42,230
ViewBag internally inserts data into the ViewBagDictionary.

49
00:02:42,450 --> 00:02:44,370
So the key of ViewData,

50
00:02:44,370 --> 00:02:47,880
and property of ViewBag must not match

51
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:50,883
because both of them will go to the same entity.

52
00:02:52,830 --> 00:02:55,170
Now, before I wrap up this video,

53
00:02:55,170 --> 00:02:57,570
previously we have seen TempData,

54
00:02:57,570 --> 00:02:59,820
which are used to generate alerts,

55
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:03,030
and TempData can be used to store data

56
00:03:03,030 --> 00:03:06,420
between two consecutive requests.

57
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:10,590
TempData internally use Session to store the data.

58
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:13,740
So think of it as a short lived session,

59
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:17,370
which will only exist for one request.

60
00:03:17,370 --> 00:03:21,780
Now, TempData value must also be type cast before use.

61
00:03:21,780 --> 00:03:26,780
So check for null values to avoid any runtime errors.

62
00:03:26,970 --> 00:03:29,220
Finally, as you already know,

63
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:33,330
TempData can be used to store only onetime message

64
00:03:33,330 --> 00:03:36,420
like error messages or validation message.

65
00:03:36,420 --> 00:03:41,130
And if you refresh the page after that, it will go away.

66
00:03:41,130 --> 00:03:44,640
So that gives you a brief idea on all the differences

67
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:48,180
between Viewbag, ViewData, and TempData.

